					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11994500#post-4268271</guid>
				<title>SCPs that were removed from the tale</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11994500/mothers-day#post-4268271</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 01 Jun 2019 14:56:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Purplayoss</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5227700</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There are a few SCPs that I was going to include in this tale, but had problems with. Here they are</p> <ul> <li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-646">SCP-646</a>: This segment was going to be from the perspective of the human female that SCP-646 once gave birth to, but I couldn't make it have the right feel.</li> <li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3578">SCP-3578</a>: I next tried to have a story from the perspective of SCP-3578-A-31 on mother's day but ran into the same problem I had with SCP-646.</li> <li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-2599">SCP-2599</a>: I had a segment written where SCP-2599 is tired after testing and thinking about how she'll never see her family again but a reviewer suggested I remove it and I did because it was boring.</li> </ul> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
